{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":26900,"record_hash":"sha256:e48111f7449b444a2288dc6caf7f9a3844f3ea9f7baaa28fd2e6495b769d41b2","timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:51:56.784Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes, I think this is the right diagnosis. `TranscriptRecord` is currently half normalized schema, half raw Codex envelope. That is why it feels weird: the “useful” fields are not enough to render or hand off the session, so consumers still have to understand `source_record.payload`.\n\nI’d organize it around one rule:\n\n`source_record` is provenance, not the product schema.\n\nA better POC shape would be something like:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n  \"record_index\": 407,\n  \"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-07T11:06:41.939Z\",\n\n  \"kind\": \"tool_call\",\n  \"source_event_kind\": \"response_item:function_call\",\n  \"role\": null,\n\n  \"text\": null,\n  \"tool_name\": \"exec_command\",\n  \"tool_input\": \"{\\\"cmd\\\":\\\"sed -n ...\\\"}\",\n\n  \"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nAnd the message example becomes:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"kind\": \"message\",\n  \"source_event_kind\": \"response_item:message\",\n  \"role\": \"assistant\",\n  \"text\": \"The spec set is nicely contained...\",\n  \"tool_name\": null,\n  \"tool_input\": null,\n  \"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nThe important shift is adding a small normalized `kind` field:\n`message`, `tool_call`, `tool_result`, `session`, `context`, `other`.\n\nI know we previously questioned `event_category`, but this is slightly different: it would not be decorative. It gives future readers a cross-agent way to render/query the transcript without knowing Codex or Claude internals. `source_event_kind` keeps the provider-specific detail.\n\nFor Claude, this maps pretty naturally:\n- Claude `user` / `assistant` message text -> `kind: \"message\"`, `text`\n- Claude `tool_use` block -> `kind: \"tool_call\"`, `tool_name`, `tool_input`\n- Claude `tool_result` block -> `kind: \"tool_result\"`, `text`\n\nI’d also rename `content_text` to just `text`. It is shorter and more honest: it can be message text, tool result text, or a normalized summary when that is all we have.\n\nPOC-sized direction:\n1. Add `kind`.\n2. Rename `event_kind` to `source_event_kind`.\n3. Rename `content_text` to `text`.\n4. Add `tool_input`.\n5. Improve Codex extraction for content arrays so assistant/user messages stop having `text: null`.\n\nThat keeps raw provenance, but makes the stored record usable without re-parsing provider JSON.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:51:56.784Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}